===Etymology===
{{Gr.}} ''di-'' two; ''meros'' part
===Noun===
'''dimer'''

#{{chemistry}} A [[molecule]] consisting of two identical halves, formed by joining two identical molecules, sometimes with a single [[atom]] acting as a [[bridge]]

